Before I go there, I would like to know about the way to solo there at level 49.<br>
Where to hunt, where to rest, how to pull and such.<br>
I got the CS tooth so I can TP there, is the TP safe?<br>
Thanks<br>
 <p><STRONG>Kanary Stormseed</STRONG><BR>Dark Elf Wizard - Vallon Zek<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ualodarnsoulburner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alodarn Soulburner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.united-kingdoms.org.uk/sig/staff.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/01 3:12:43 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.united-kingdoms.org.uk/sig/alodarn.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in CS at level 49, how?</span><hr size=1> Depends, if like me you are pro-dragon, it's very safe.<br>
<br>
If your not...it's a lottery as to if you can get Invis off quickly enough.<br>
<br>
And now they have changed the Otters aggro code, you can't train the drakes to them and get the Otters to take them out for you.<br>
<br>
Drakes are bad, they have a really large AE cold breath that is simply brutal.<br>
<br>
Apart from that, yep, the Wyverns are nice xp at 49-50.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
Also its nice being able to port to any of the Velious ports without having to worry - Dragons forever. (well apart from the Ring of Scale, they drop phat lewt) <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://www.united-kingdoms.org.uk/sig/alodarn.gif"></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.united-kingdoms.org.uk"><IMG SRC="http://www.united-kingdoms.org.uk/sig/alodarn-desc.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/01 5:42:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in CS at level 49, how?</span><hr size=1> SoW / Levitate and RUN FORREST RUN!<br>
<br>
I usually just run right off the cliff and if Drakes aggro I follow the beach in as straight a line as I can, eventually the Drakes will go back to their spawn. No problem.<br>
<br>
Just don't stand around long enough to get hit by 2 AEs or you're dead.<br>
<br>
I've found that CT, SF and WL port-in spots are a lot more difficult and risky than CS.<br>
 <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig52.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/01 1:21:29 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in CS at level 49, how?</span><hr size=1> I've found Wyverns in CS to be great solo XP from level 44 on up (I'm 1/2 blue from 49, I can't wait to get home!). The real nice part is that you'll start accumulating quest gems. The only problem is that sometimes spawns get thin, and you have to sit at FM for a while, waiting for a repop.<br>
<br>
The single best thing you can do to prepare for hunting in CS is to get up to Dubious with CoV. I frequently /dance with Drakes after porting in. I can med on the berach while someone kites a Wyvern by in complete safety. If someone does train a Drake to you, you can just back away to avoid future AE hits, and it won't come back for you after the other guy gates/dies.<br>
<br>
If I have Steelskin up, I can take 2 Drake AEs no prob. Usually, though, I just run out of range after the first blast, so it's just an extra level of safety, not a requirement. <p>Zwobu &lt;Trade Foundation&gt; Innoruuk<br><img src="http://patriot.net/~josh/zwobu.jpeg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uverbalsabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Verbalsabre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 7:14:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in CS at level 49, how?</span><hr size=1> Love this zone and went from 44 to 49 there by just pulling Wyverns to beach and kiting them up and down BUT you do have to make sure there are no drakes nearby when you pull. Good faction or no, I am amiable, the drakes will jump in if they see you pull the wyvern. <br>
<br>
As soon as you get to 49 pack up and head to LOIO. There are some ruins at loc 0,0 at each corner of the ruins you will find a pair of bloodgills. These are OMG experiece. Went through 49 and 50 in about 12 played hours combined, usually with no Clarity. One IC will take a bloodgill down to where he is running, finish him with a baby nuke. Just fire til you are oom and never get attacked or have to run. If you get a resist just let him beat on your steelskin while you root him then back off and launch IC again. Make sure you have lev up though so that if you do manage to get into a bad situation you can swim up to above water and run for safety (did this when I accidently wandered to close and agro'd 2 at once while LOM.) <br>
<br>
Once you hit 51 time to head back to CS. Hopefully you have Temp Flux staff (did the quest start to finish in about 6 hours) plus you will need Pillar of Frost and Shackles or BoF. Use staff to agro 4 wyverns, round them up, snare, Pillar to death. Make sure that when you go to snare they are not next to the otters (something I learned the hard way.) Just started the quadding portion of this pattern and 51 is flying by for me. My friend following these steps went straight to 55 in no time.<br>
<br>
GOOD LUCK!!<br>
 <p>Verbalsabre, 
51th Wizard,  
Phoenix Horizon,  
Zebuxorok 

</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=59.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=48.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=74.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=74.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=74.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=74.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilation